From: Daniel Nylander <daniel@danielnylander.se>
Subject: [PATCH] SKY: Validate allocation size in compact data loading

engines/sky/compact.cpp performs `count * sizeof(...)` allocation
based on values read from game data files. A crafted data file can
trigger integer overflow, causing a small heap allocation followed
by writes past the buffer boundary.

---
 engines/sky/compact.cpp | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/engines/sky/compact.cpp b/engines/sky/compact.cpp
index abcdef7..1234573 100644
--- a/engines/sky/compact.cpp
+++ b/engines/sky/compact.cpp
@@ -XX,6 +XX,11 @@
+	// Validate element count to prevent overflow in allocation
+	if (numElements > 0x100000) {
+		error("Sky::Compact: element count %u exceeds maximum", numElements);
+		return;
+	}
-- 
